>Limited license to use Platform</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>We grant you a limited license to access and make personal use of the<span lang=\"EN-IN\">Platform</span>, but not to copy, duplicate, modify it, or any portion of it. This license does not include any resale or commercial use of the Platform or its Contents; any collection and use of any product listings, descriptions or prices; any derivative use of the Platform or its Contents; any downloading or copying of account information for the benefit of another user, or any use of data mining, robots or similar data gathering and extract on tools.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span lang=\"EN-IN\">You agree to maintain all copyright, trademark and other notices on the Content. You may not copy, transmit, reproduce, publicly display, perform, distribute, alter, transmit or create derivative works of any Content or any portion of or excerpts from the Content in any fashion that is not authorized by us in writing or expressly permitted in these Terms of Use.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>5.</strong><strong><span lang=\"EN-IN\">Services on the Platform</span></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span lang=\"EN-IN\">Based on the subscription model opted by you, you will receive limited rights to access the Platform, and will be able to perform all such activities and receive all such benefits, as part of the relevant subscription model (collectively, the &ldquo;<strong>Services</strong>&rdquo;). For details on the subscription-based Services we offer, please refer to the</span><span lang=\"EN-IN\"><a href=\"https://www.trasers.com/usage-policy\">usage policy</a></span><span lang=\"EN-IN\">.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><span lang=\"EN-IN\">6.</span></strong><strong><span lang=\"EN-IN\">Access to the Platform, Content and Security</span></strong></p>\r\n<p><span lang=\"EN-IN\">We endeavour to make the Platform and/ or the Content available at all times. However, we do not represent that access to the Platform and/ or the Content will be uninterrupted, timely, error free, free of viruses or other harmful components or that such defects will be corrected.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang=\"EN-IN\">We do not warrant that the Platform and/ or the Content will be compatible with all hardware and software which you may use. We shall not be liable for damage to, or viruses or other code that may affect, any equipment (including but not limited to your mobile device), software, data or other property as a result of your download, installation, access to or use of the Platform and/ or the Content or your obtaining any material from, or as a result of using the Platform and/ or the Content. We shall also not be liable for the actions of third parties. We reserve the right to suspend or withdraw access to the Platform and/ or any of it&rsquo;s the Content to you personally, or to all Users temporarily or permanently at any time without notice.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><span lang=\"EN-IN\">7.</span></strong><strong><span lang=\"EN-IN\">Restricted Content</span></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span lang=\"EN-IN\">Access to certain areas of the Platform is restricted (&ldquo;<strong>Restricted Content</strong>&rdquo;) to exclusive clients of ours, and/ or such other individuals/ entities having an arrangement with us for this purpose (including without limitation, restricted/ limited access through subscription models, account specific/ password protected accesses, etc.). You are not authorized to access any password-restricted areas unless you have received a password from us (or from your employer if your employer has been authorized by us to issue such password). You may not use another person&rsquo;s password to access the Platform.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span lang=\"EN-IN\">If you have been issued or given access to any Content though a password, you are responsible for keeping your password confidential. You agree not to share your password with any other individuals or to otherwise allow any other individuals to access the Platform or the Content through your account. You further agree not to reproduce, publicly display, perform, distribute, alter, transmit, create derivative works from or otherwise share any Content or portions or excerpts thereof from Restricted Content with any other individuals or third parties, except as expressly provided in these Terms of Use or any contract executed by you for this purpose. You take full responsibility for any activity that occurs through the use of your account and you agree to notify us immediately if you become aware that any other individual has accessed your account or has obtained your password. To protect the security of the Platform and your account, we reserve the right to monitor the Platform usage and suspend access to any account with activity we deem suspicious. If your account is suspended, we will contact you to ensure that your account has not been compromised before reactivating your access.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><span lang=\"EN-IN\">8.</span></strong><strong><span lang=\"EN-IN\">Further restrictions on use of Platform and Content</span></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span lang=\"EN-IN\">You hereby consent and agree not to (a) violate the security of the Platform nor attempt to gain unauthorized access to Platform or any of its Content, including without limitation any data, materials, information, computer systems or networks connected to any server associated with the Platform, through hacking, password timing or any other means; (b) take nor attempt any action that, in our sole discretion, imposes or may impose an unreasonable or disproportionately large burden on the Platform or its infrastructure; (c) use nor attempt to use any &ldquo;scraper,&rdquo; &ldquo;robot,&rdquo; &ldquo;bot,&rdquo; &ldquo;spider,&rdquo; &ldquo;data mining,&rdquo; &ldquo;computer code,&rdquo; or any other automated device, program, tool, algorithm, process or methodology to access, acquire, copy, or monitor any portion of the Platform, any data or content found on or accessed through the Platform without our prior written consent; and (d) forge headers or otherwise manipulate identifiers in order to disguise the origin of any other Content.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>9.</strong><strong>Accuracy of Information</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span lang=\"EN-IN\">While the information contained on the Platform has been obtained from sources believed to be reliable, we disclaim all warranties as to the accuracy, completeness, reliability or adequacy of such information. The Content on the Platform is based on our reasonable efforts to compile and analyse the best sources reasonably available to us at any given time. Any opinions reflect our judgment at the time and are subject to change. You assume sole responsibility for the selection of the Content to achieve any of your intended results, and your sole and exclusive remedy for any alleged loss or damage suffered by you in connection with your use of the Platform or the Content is to discontinue using the Platform.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>10.</strong><strong>Third Party Links</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span lang=\"EN-IN\">This Platform may contain links to other third party Platforms, which are provided as additional resources for the convenience of the Users. We do not endorse, sponsor or accept any responsibility for these third party Platforms, and the User agrees to direct any concerns relating to these third party Platforms to the relevant Platform administrator.</span></p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p><strong><span lang=\"EN-IN\">11.</span></strong><strong><span lang=\"EN-IN\">Choice of Users</span></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>You may request alteration/ deletion of your personal data or information that may be collected by us, but please note that we may be required (by law or otherwise) to keep this information and not delete it (or to keep this information for a certain time, in which case we will comply with your deletion request in accordance with our Privacy Policy and in the ordinary course only after we have fulfilled such requirements). When we delete any information, it will be deleted from the active database, but may remain in the archives.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>12.</strong><strong>Intellectual Property Rights</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>All Content included on the Platform, such as text, graphics, logos, button icons, images, audio clips, digital downloads, data compilations, software,<span lang=\"EN-IN\">and/or other works or materials including research publications, opinions, data analysis, statistics</span>is our property, or the property of our affiliates or content suppliers, and is protected by Indian and international intellectual property law, including copyright, authors&rsquo; rights and database rights laws. The compilation of all the Content on our Platform is our exclusive property, and is protected by laws of India and international copyright and database right laws. All software used on the Platform is also our exclusive property, or the property of our affiliates or software suppliers, and is protected by Indian and international copyright and authors&rsquo; rights laws.<span lang=\"EN-IN\"> </span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>13.</strong><strong>Privacy</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>By using this Platform, you agree to be bound by and abide by the terms and conditions of our<span lang=\"EN-IN\"><a href=\"https://www.trasers.com/privacy-policy\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">Privacy Policy</span></a></span>, the terms of which are incorporated into, and form a crucial part of, these Terms of Use. Our Privacy Policy sets out<span lang=\"EN-IN\">information on our data privacy compliances, and the practices and policies, including the safety standards and measures implemented by us in this regard, including due compliance measures and observance of the provisions of the EU General Data Protection Regulation, as applicable. It also</span>sets out the terms on which we process any personal or financial data or information we collect from you, or that you provide to us. Our Privacy Policy shall also apply to your use of our Platform and by using our Platform, you consent to such processing and you warrant that all data provided by you is accurate.<strong></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>14.</strong><strong>Further User Assurance</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span lang=\"EN-IN\">By using our Platform and/ or any of its Content, you represent and warrant that all information you submit, including without limitation, any registration or subscription details, is truthful, lawful and accurate and that you agree to maintain the accuracy of such information. You further represent and warrant that your use of the Platform and/ or any of its Content shall be solely for your personal use and you shall not authorize others to use your account, including your profile or email address and that you are solely responsible for all content published or displayed through your account, including any email messages, and your interactions with other Users and you shall abide by all applicable local, state, national and foreign laws, treaties and regulations, including those related to data privacy, international communications and the transmission of technical or personal data.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span lang=\"EN-IN\">All necessary licenses, consents, permissions and rights are owned by you and there is no need for any payment or permission or authorization required from any other party or entity to use the Platform and/ or any of its Content.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><span lang=\"EN-IN\">15.</span></strong><strong><span lang=\"EN-IN\">Termination</span></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span lang=\"EN-IN\">In accessing and using our Platform, you agree to comply with all applicable laws and further agree not to take any action that would compromise the security or viability of our Platform. We reserve the sole right to terminate any of the User&rsquo;s access to the Platform at any time for any reason. The terms hereunder regarding Accuracy of Information, Limitation of Liability and Indemnity shall survive termination.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><span lang=\"EN-IN\">16.</span></strong><strong><span lang=\"EN-IN\">Limitation of Liability</span></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>In no event will we, or our directors, employees, agents, licensors, partners or suppliers be liable to you for any special, indirect, incidental, consequential, punitive, reliance, or exemplary damages (including without limitation lost business opportunities, lost revenues, or loss of anticipated profits or any other pecuniary or non-pecuniary loss or damage of any nature whatsoever) arising out of or relating to (a) these Terms of Use; or (b) your use or inability to use the Platform or any of its Content. In no event will we or any of our contractors, directors, employees, agents, third party partners, licensors or suppliers&rsquo; total liability to you for all damages, liabilities, losses, and causes of action arising out of or relating to (a) these Terms of Use; or (b) your use or inability to use the Platform or any of its Content; or (c) any other interactions with us, however caused and whether arising in contract, tort including negligence, warranty or otherwise, exceed the amount paid by you, if any, for using the portion of the Platform or any of its Content. In no event will we or any of our contractors, directors, employees, agents, third party partners, licensors or suppliers be liable to you for any losses, damage, liabilities, and causes of action arising out of any act, omission or negligence to which you contributed.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><span lang=\"EN-IN\">17.</span></strong><strong><span lang=\"EN-IN\">Indemnity</span></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>You agree to indemnify, save and hold us and our affiliates, contractors, employees officers, directors, agents and third party partners harmless from any and all claims, losses, damages, liabilities, costs and expenses, including without limitation, legal fees and expenses arising out of or related to your use or misuse of the Platform or any of its Content, any violation of these Terms of Use, or any of the covenants made by you herein.</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n<p><strong>18.</strong><strong>Governing Law and Jurisdiction</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>These Terms of Use are governed by, and construed in accordance with the laws of India. You agree, as we do, to submit to the exclusive jurisdiction of courts in Bangalore, India.<strong></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>19.</strong><strong>Grievance Officer</strong></p>\r\n<p>The name and contact details of our Grievance Officer are as follows:<strong></strong></p>\r\n<p>Ganesh Arunachala</p>\r\n<p>Vice President - Chief Assurance Officer - Corporate Data Protection</p>\r\n<p>2350 Mission College Blvd., Suite 1250, Santa Clara, CA 95054</p>\r\n<p>E-Mail:<span lang=\"EN-IN\"><a href=\"mailto:ganesh.arunachala@trasers.com\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">ganesh.arunachala@trasers.com</span></a></span></p>\r\n<p>The Grievance Officer can be contacted to report abuse, or to complain against any content hosted, transmitted, published, updated or shared on our Platform.</p>\r\n');
