(527, 'Help', 2, 'custom', '', '_sys_block_type_raw_1546603022', 13, 2147483647, '0', 'raw', '<div class=\"bx-page-faq-block2\">\r\n<div class=\"bx-page-faq-block2-header\">\r\n  Contribution guidelines\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"bx-page-faq-block2-intro\">\r\n	<p>Trasers+  is all about driving productive conversations and exchanging ideas. To help you  make the most of it, here are a set of guidelines.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<p><strong>Dont hold back</strong></p>\r\n<p>Trasers+  is designed to facilitate an exchange of innovative ideas, and we all know  innovation can come across as unusual, unconventional, crazy. As Larry Page  once said, Good ideas are always crazy until they are not. So, dont hold  back, challenge the unorthodox, and help propel the businesses to become more  adaptable, innovative, and engaging. </p>\r\n<p><strong>KISS</strong></p>\r\n<p>Or  keep it short and simple as they call it! After all, so many things are vying  for everyones attention these days. Stay focused on your main idea and include  all the essential details. Also, refrain from sharing any third-party  commercial link or URL.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Avoid self-promotion</strong></p>\r\n<p>You  are most welcome to share content or ideas from your website or blog. But we expect you to be mindful of the fine line between  talking with people and talking at them. As we said, great conversation and  exchange of ideas are vital for Trasers+ community.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Invite collaboration</strong></p>\r\n<p>Innovation  doesnt happen in a vacuum. We encourage you to invite suggestions from the  group to help you advance your ideas. At the same time, you must also reciprocate.  After all, a community is all about bringing people together in ways that allow  them to do things they couldn\'t have done in isolation.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Be inclusive</strong></p>\r\n<p>Diversity  fuels innovation. Sometimes, different perspectives can bring a sense of discomfort.  Encourage all voices, help new perspectives be heard, listen actively, and keep  the discussion respectful. Value others ideas, styles, and viewpoints.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Be pragmatic </strong></p>\r\n<p>We  understand your enthusiasm to bounce ideas off in the group but ensure to back  them up with data. In complex stream of conversations, sometimes its difficult  to gauge the difference between ideas born out of learning, and that of pure  fantasy (not to say that fantasy isnt constructive; after all, someone did  think of flying objects and then the airplane was invented!). Structure your  idea to gain traction within the community.</p>\r\n<p><strong>No inappropriate content </strong></p>\r\n<p>  As  a community, its important that we maintain a sense of decorum and respect  within the group. We urge you to refrain from posting any content that could be  deemed as inappropriate including religious, political, offensive, misleading,  fraudulent, threatening, defamatory, illegal or discriminatory. After all,  happy communities are thriving communities! </p>\r\n</div>', 1, 1, 1, 0),
